review_blob: an average pale ale, I like the look of the bottle, but the beer was just ok.  poured a clear honey color with little head.  I could taste the hops and a bit of a citrus undertone.  aroma was good, left a bitter taste on the palate.
this was the first mocha beer I have tried.  I am not a coffee drinker so I didnt like this beer at all.  I probably will not try this style of beer again.
pour was a clear carmel color.  little to no head.  test is very barleyie.  not a favorite of mine, probably will not try it again.
beer_name: Heavy Seas Mutiny Fleet Below Decks

review_blob: bottle.  clear deep brown color, little to now head.  Malty flavor, very nice on the palate, high alcohol content, also very good out of the keg.
pours a fadded purple and is cloudy orange in the glass.  has a lot of head and bubbles almost like a carbonated coke.  not really natural tasting.  best to drink this one very cold.
this is a great beer if you can find it.  You need to talk to older cincinnati citizens.  I found a guy who had a can in the back of his fridge.  Great beer. they should really start making it again.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: pours nice, clear golden color without much head.  The aroma is definately apple and spice, too bad the taste doesnt match.  The flavor comes on strong.  leaves a strong flavor on your palate.  This would be a great beer for a nonbeer drinker.
